{"key":"post-5554569","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>5554569</id>\n<content>Another tip to make the gauge last much longer is to get it away from the heat.  You can get one of these loops at any local boiler/pipefitting shop.  They didn't have the 1/8' npt size of the gauge, so I used 1/4&quot; npt and reducing bells.  This keeps the pressure gauge at nearly room temperature.  The one I am using is a cheapie air tank gauge, not a steam one because it's no longer exposed to heat.  It only cost six bucks.&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/06-17/598408768-pressure_guage_002a.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/06-17/598408768-thumb_pressure_guage_002a.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>5555955</next>\n<prev>5554329</prev>\n<first>5551931</first>\n<last>5557708</last>\n<when>1145984108</when>\n<utime>04/25/06 07:55 PM</utime>\n</post>"}